      </main>
    </>
  );
}


5. Internationalization (i18n)

Routing: The site MUST use sub-path routing for languages (e.g., /en/, /es/). This will be handled by a [lang] dynamic segment in src/app/.


No Hardcoded Text: No user-facing text MUST be hardcoded in any component. All strings MUST be pulled from translation JSON files.

we will have 2 languages, English and Spanish.
6. Animation

Provider: We will use framer-motion for all UI animations.

Uniformity: An AnimationProvider.tsx MUST be created in src/providers/ to wrap the application.

Centralized Variants: Common animations (e.g., fadeIn, slideInUp) MUST be defined as variants in a central file (e.g., src/lib/animations.ts) and imported into components. This ensures all animations are uniform and easily editable.

7. Data Fetching & Mutations

Fetching: Data fetching MUST be done in Server Components using await fetch(). This takes advantage of Next.js 16's automatic caching and deduplication.

Mutations: Form submissions and data mutations MUST use Server Actions. Do not create separate API routes for simple form handling. This is the modern, simpler, and more performant standard.

8. Tooling & Quality

Code Style: The project MUST use Prettier for code formatting and ESLint for code linting.

Pre-Commit Hook: A pre-commit hook (using husky) MUST be set up to run eslint --fix and prettier --write before any code is committed. This ensures 100% code consistency.

TypeScript: any is forbidden. All types MUST be explicitly defined. All component props MUST be typed.

Named Exports: All components and functions MUST use named exports. Do not use export default. This improves refactoring and findability in the IDE.

9. UI & Responsiveness

Mobile-First & Fully Responsive: All components and pages MUST be built with a mobile-first approach. The design MUST be fully responsive and pixel-perfect across all common breakpoints, from small mobile devices (320px) up to large desktop screens (1440px+).

Tailwind Breakpoints: Use standard Tailwind CSS breakpoints (sm, md, lg, xl, 2xl) for responsive design. Do not use custom media queries unless absolutely necessary and documented.

No Horizontal Scroll: At no screen width may horizontal scrolling occur.

Fluid Typography & Spacing: Use responsive typography (e.g., text-lg, md:text-xl) and spacing (e.g., p-4, md:p-8) to ensure the UI scales gracefully.